wikipedia_page.main: Susannah Jane Rankin  (26 November 1897 – 24 July 1989, née Ellis) was a Welsh Congregational minister, religious educator, linguist and translator. She spent time as a missionary in Papua New Guinea. She translated works from Welsh and English to the Motu language.

response: * The Reverend Susannah Jane Rankin. For services to the people of Papua and New Guinea.
